Step 1: Identify the values from the statement.  
• Net Profit = -1,352,379.63  
• Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = -7,724,112.71  

Step 2: Use the formula:  
  Operating Cash Flow to Net Income Ratio = (Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities) / (Net Profit)  

Note: As both values are negative, the ratio will be positive.  

Step 3: Calculate the ratio:  
  Ratio = (-7,724,112.71) / (-1,352,379.63) ≈ 5.71  

Thus, the Operating Cash Flow to Net Income Ratio is 5.71.
